      <section eId="sec_20_2_7">
        <num>20-2-7</num>
        <content>
          <p>The members of the State Board of Education as a committee or any committee of the state board may hold committee meetings anywhere within or outside this state when necessary to obtain information for future guidance of the state board; provided, however, that no action of the state board shall be of force and effect unless such action is taken at a regular or called meeting of the state board.</p>
          <p>(Ga. L. 1953, Jan.-Feb. Sess., p. 110, ยง 1; Ga. L. 2012, p. 358, ยง 3/HB 706.)</p>
